A fuller comparative examination of early Latin MSS. may strengthen the supposition that cases of apparently careless spelling may be really due not to accident, but to different modes of pronunciation current in the regions to which the MS. or its ancestors belonged: and thus the orthography of a MS. may throw great lighton the origin of the text which it presents. 1 have therefore collected some of the more regularly recurring cases of peculiar orthography in q.
